    <h1>
        <a href="search/search-acr-directory.aspx">Meet Your Fellow Members</a></h1>
    <div class="member">
        <div id="bio">
            <img id="MainContent_acrMemberBio_imgMemberImage" title="CLAUDIU DIMOFTE, San Diego State University" src="assets/images/member_photos/3762.jpg" alt="CLAUDIU DIMOFTE" width="82" />
            
            <div id="bio-link">
                <a id="MainContent_acrMemberBio_hlProfileLink" href="web/member/profile.aspx?MemberId=3762">
                View Profile</a>
            </div>
            
        </div>
        <p>
            <div id="bio-name">
                <span id="MainContent_acrMemberBio_lblMemberName">CLAUDIU DIMOFTE</span>
            </div>
            <br />
            <span id="MainContent_acrMemberBio_lblMemberBio">
  Claudiu Dimofte (Ph.D., University of Washington 2004) is faculty at SDSU in beautiful San Diego, CA. His research interests include implicit consumer cognition (e.g., unconscious processing   of brand information), marketing metrics (e.g., scale development and   validation), international marketing (e.g., cross-cultural consumer   response to global brands), and the interface of marketing with   operations and finance (e.g., consumer response to modular products and   brand equity effects on stock performance). His research has been   published in academic journals including the <em>Journal of Consumer Psychology,</em> the <em>Journal of Consumer Research, Management Science,</em> and the <em>International Journal of Research in Marketing.</em> He serves on the Editorial Board of the <em>Journal of Consumer Psychology</em> and teaches the core marketing course in SDSU's MBA program.    
</span>
        </p>
    </div>
